<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Mr. Roboto - missing changelog</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <link
      href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway:400,700'
      rel='stylesheet'
      type='text/css'/>
  <style>
    a {
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:link {
      color: white;
    }
    a:visited {
      color: white;
    }
    .alert {
      color: brown;
    }
    .plone {
      background-color: rgb(0,149,211);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body class="plone">
  <h1>Pull request missing a change log entry</h1>
  <p>Every change made in plone, specially the ones made through a pull request,
  is worth noting it down on the change log file (usually <em>CHANGES.rst</em>).</p>
  
  <p>Some packages, at least <strong>plone.app.upgrade</strong> and <strong>Products.CMFPlone</strong>
    are using <a href="https://pypi.org/project/towncrier/">towncrier</a>, so rather than editing <em>CHANGES.rst</em>
    one should add a file inside the <strong>news</strong> folder. See an <a href="https://community.plone.org/t/using-towncrier-for-changes-rst-in-plone-packages/6486">outline of how to use it</a>.

  <p>Thanks to this change log entries it is easier to know what happened on a given package,
  who has been lately working on it, etc.</p>

  <p>So please, add a change log entry <em>:-)</em></p>

</body>
</html>
